description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Independent Reviewing Officer &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;58870 CHEE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Whiting Road, Norwich&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;£21,360 to £23,317 per annum (Scale L)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;18.5 hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Temporary contract to cover maternity leave&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Independent Reviewing Officer required to chair Looked After Children Reviews/Child Protection Conferences. Enthusiastic person required to join the Independent Statutory Service committed to providing better outcomes for children. The Independent Statutory Services is a county wide service and as Independent Reviewing Officers we operate out of several different venues within the County.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The place of work for this position is Whiting Road in Norwich, although you could work from different venues due to us working in a POD system. The PODs we have in this service are Norwich &amp; South, West &amp; Breckland &amp; North, East &amp; Broadland.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position is a part-time, temporary post to cover maternity within the North, East &amp; Broadland POD although you may be required to travel to any venue within Norfolk.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All our office-based roles are currently working from home as part of our Smarter Working plans and to support the health and safety of all our colleagues. We anticipate that working remotely will be a key feature of this role and when offices re-open your office base will be Whiting Road, Norwich.  Our technology platform and equipment is first class, enabling you to connect and collaborate remotely. We ask that you have in place good Broadband connectivity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews will take place via video technology, where you will have the opportunity to discuss these working arrangements.&lt;/p&gt;
